  "title": "Core: register HtmlAdapter in Rust document format registry",
  "description": "Add HtmlAdapter to crates/jit/src/document/adapter.rs implementing the DocFormatAdapter trait, then register it in AdapterRegistry::with_builtins(). Part of story abfd6016. Independent of sibling tasks (a), (b), (c).\n\n## Implementation\n\n1. pub struct HtmlAdapter; impl DocFormatAdapter:\n   - id() → \"html\"\n   - supports_path() → extension html or htm (case-insensitive, same Path::new(path).extension() pattern as MarkdownAdapter)\n   - detect() → starts with <!doctype html (case-insensitive, leading-whitespace tolerant) or contains <html (case-insensitive)\n   - scan_assets() → regex extract src/href attribute values; same filter rules as MarkdownAdapter (exclude mailto:, anchor-only; strip fragment; include external URLs)\n   - rewrite_links → leave at trait default (unimplemented) — same as MarkdownAdapter\n2. Register HtmlAdapter in AdapterRegistry::with_builtins() after MarkdownAdapter.\n3. Re-export HtmlAdapter from crates/jit/src/document/mod.rs.\n4. Unit tests for the adapter and for registry resolution.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] HtmlAdapter.id() == \"html\" — covered by a test.\n- [ ] supports_path returns true for foo.html, foo.htm, FOO.HTML, dir/bar.html; false for foo.md, foo.txt, foo.html.bak, extensionless paths — covered by a test.\n- [ ] detect returns true on a string starting with <!DOCTYPE html> and on a string containing <html> (with or without leading whitespace, mixed case); false on plain text, a markdown fixture, and empty string — covered by tests.\n- [ ] scan_assets on a reveal.js-style fixture with a <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"…\">, an <img src=\"https://…\">, an <a href=\"#slide\">, and a <script src=\"…\"> returns the stylesheet path and the img URL and the script src, excludes the anchor-only href — covered by a test.\n- [ ] AdapterRegistry::with_builtins().resolve(\"foo.html\", \"\") returns an adapter whose id() == \"html\" — covered by a test.\n- [ ] AdapterRegistry::with_builtins().resolve(\"foo.md\", \"\") still returns the markdown adapter — covered by a test (ensures ordering is safe).\n- [ ] jit document add <issue> <path/to/file.html> on a fresh fixture results in the stored DocumentReference having format == \"html\" — verified manually or via an integration test; existing add_document_reference tests continue to pass.\n- [ ] No migration of existing stored DocumentReference.format values (retroactive fix-up is a separate follow-up).\n- [ ] cargo-ci gate passes (cargo fmt --check && cargo clippy -D warnings && cargo test --workspace all green).\n- [ ] code-review gate passes.",
